  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "Expressing your feelings to someone can be nerve-wracking, but it's important to approach the situation thoughtfully and considerately. Here are some steps you can take to tell her that you like her:\n\n1. **Build a Connection**: Spend time getting to know her better and building a friendship. This will help you feel more comfortable around her and may make it easier to express your feelings.\n\n2. **Gauge Her Interest**: Try to observe how she interacts with you. Does she seem interested in spending time with you? Does she give you signs that she might feel the same way? Understanding her feelings can give you more confidence.\n\n3. **Choose the Right Time and Place**: Find a moment when you can talk to her privately and without distractions. This will help ensure that both of you can focus on the conversation.\n\n4. **Be Honest and Respectful**: When you talk to her, be straightforward and sincere. You can say something like, \u201cI\u2019ve really enjoyed getting to know you and I wanted to let you know that I have feelings for you. I understand if you don\u2019t feel the same way, but I wanted to be honest about how I feel.\u201d\n\n5. **Be Prepared for Any Response**: Understand that she might need time to process what you\u2019ve said, or she might not feel the same way. Be prepared for any reaction and respect her feelings regardless.\n\n6. **Practice Self-Care**: Remember that expressing your feelings is an act of courage, and take care of yourself emotionally, regardless of the outcome.\n\n7. **Consider Alternatives**: If speaking directly feels too intimidating, you could also write her a heartfelt letter or message. This allows you to convey your feelings without the pressure of an immediate response.\n\nGood luck, and remember that being open and honest is important, not just for this situation but for your growth as an individual.",
